IN LAST THREE (3) YEARS WE HAVE SUBSTANTIALLY REDUCED OUR CHLORINE INVENTORY FROM INITIAL QUANTITY OF 10,000. lbs TO DOWN TO 4,000. lbs BECAUSE OF LOW BUSINESS ACTIVITY AND CHANGE OF PRODUCT MIX.



Our corporate policy at Aurora Circuits, Inc., requires establishing programs and utilizing written procedures to cover the actions that management and employees shall take to ensure the following:

a) accidental toxic release prevention; 

b) prompt and sufficient emergency response to fire, chemical spills, or gas release;

c) safety at the facility;

d) implementation of safe procedures.  

Our senior management is committed to protecting our employees, the surrounding community, and environment from accidental toxic release and pollution.



Aurora Circuits, Inc., Inc., is a manufacturer of printed circuit boards to industrial, including automotive,  businesses.  Our company is certified to ISO 9001-2008, which demonstrates our compliance to world-wide and automotive quality system standards.  Our facility in Aurora was constructed and opened in 1996 to service high-volume requirements of our customers in single-sided printed circuit boards.  We use several regulated chemicals to process our products which include various polymer and thermal inks, hydrochloric acid, chlorine gas, weak acid fluxes, and proprietary sodium persulfate and sodium hydroxide solutions.



